CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 11, 1954, pg. 7, reads: "Carver Week Committee - Plans for the annual observance of George Washington Carver Week to be observed during the first week in January, were being made Monday when this committee in charge of arrangements met in Conference Room on the eleventh floor of the Civic Building, 200 Ross Street. Left to right: Dr. Hedwig Pregler, Miss Myra Johns, Mrs. Israel Oseroff, Mrs. Mary K. Marshall, Mrs. Alma Illery, Mrs. Lillian A. Friedberg, Miss Lula L. West, Mrs. Goldie Hamilton, Mrs. W. C. Eichenlaub and Mrs. Georgia Paylor. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: Dr. Hedwig Pregler, Myra Johns, Mrs. Israel Oseroff, Mary K. Marshall, Alma Illery, Lillian A. Friedberg, Lula L. West, Goldie Hamilton, Mrs. W. C. Eichenlaub, and Mrs. Georgia Paylor, gathered around table in Civic Building
